SIMPLE: orthographical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orthographical
<hw>Or`tho*graph"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>orthographique</ets>, L. <ets>orthographus</ets>, Gr.
<?/.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to orthography, or right
spelling; also, correct in spelling; <as>as, <ex>orthographical</ex>
rules; the letter was <ex>orthographic</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to right lines
or angles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Orthographic projection</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Orthogonal projection</b></col></mcol>, <cd>that projection
which is made by drawing lines, from every point to be projected,
perpendicular to the plane of projection. Such a projection of the
sphere represents its circles as seen in perspective by an eye supposed
to be placed at an infinite distance, the plane of projection passing
through the center of the sphere perpendicularly to the line of
sight.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orthographically</ent>⟦br⟧
